.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-EMERGENCY-STOP" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-emergency-stop \- gracefully stop the Lightning daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-emergency-stop
.SH DESCRIPTION
Sends a
.B stop
command to the daemon via
.BR lightning-cli .
All channels will be left intact; the daemon performs a clean shutdown.
Returns an error object if the daemon is unreachable.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"ok":true,"message":"daemon stopping"}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-node-health (1),
.BR lightning-daemon (1)
